                <h1>Discover Wyoming's Rich History: A Journey Through Time</h1>
                <p>Wyoming's history is rich and diverse, marked by Native American cultures, the westward expansion, and the frontier era. It became the 44th state in 1890, noted for its stunning landscapes and national parks. Key events include the Wyoming Massacre and the suffragette movement, which granted women the right to vote in 1869, the first U.S. state to do so.</p>
